In this week's episode of the Major Issues Podcast, we're diving deep into the epic crossover event "The Trial of Jean Grey" (2014)! Join us as we explore the complex and gripping storyline that sees the original Jean Grey—plucked from the past—facing trial for crimes she has yet to commit as the Phoenix. We'll discuss the emotional turmoil of the X-Men as they confront their past and future, the intergalactic politics of the Shi'ar Empire, and the cosmic-scale consequences of wielding such unimaginable power. This is one trial you won't want to miss!

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

 

